  <bioghist id="aspace_b64b43710c615a96419acba23ef4bd24">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Professor in the Department of Design and Environmental Analysis, Cornell University.</p><p> Jennings received a B.S. in Housing and Interior Design (1968) and a M.S. in Housing and Urban Studies (1969) both from Oklahoma State University.</p><p> Jenning's research interests focus on oridnary American buildings and interiors, as well as contemporary interior design history, theory, and criticism.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_b4188338c031e8282648721c8677d16b">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Exhibit items, records and related material for an exhibition researched and designed by Jennning's undergraduate and graduate students (2003-2006).</p><p> Includes slides used for teaching; prints and negatives used in her book Cheap and Tasteful Dwellings; photos and slides of student winners of various competitions (1993-2005); information about Interior Archetypes Research and Teaching Project , initiated in 1997.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_84624b9a34226168b17d462964bed2dd">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>Jan Jennings papers, #23-16-3913. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
